{
  "question_id": "37443250-8b86-4cc5-9fe1-3ce36da3f6bc",
  "short_text": "Digit 2",
  "content": "Given a number `N`, write a program to print the digit **2** in `2 * N - 1` rows using stars (`*`).\n\n```\n* * * \n    *\n* * * \n*\n* * * \n```\n\n<MultiLineNote>\nThere is a space after every star (`*`).\n</MultiLineNote>\n\n---\n\n#### Input\n\nThe input will be a single line containing an integer representing `N`.\n\n---\n\n#### Output\n\nThe output should be `2 * N - 1` rows containing stars (`*`) as the digit **2** shown in the sample output.\n\n---\n\n#### Explanation\n\n\nFor example, if the given number is `N = 5`,\n\n- Print the stars (`*`) on **9** (`2 * 5 - 1`) rows as shown in the given image.\n\n\n<Img imageSrc='https://assets.ccbp.in/frontend/content/programming-foundations/cx-digit-2.png' widthPercent='50'/>\n\n<MultiLineNote>\n\nIn the given image,\n\n- The Empty box indicates two spaces (\"&nbsp;&nbsp;\").\n- The Star in the box indicates the star and a space (\"* \").\n\n</MultiLineNote>\n\nThe output should be,\n\n```\n* * * * * \n        * \n        * \n        * \n* * * * * \n*        \n*        \n*        \n* * * * * \n```",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "a6a151cc-fa07-4843-a72e-f8e69dc571a6",
      "code_content": "n = int(input())\n\nfor row in range(1, 2 * n):\n    if row == 1 or  row == n or row == (2 * n - 1):\n        each_row = \"* \" * n\n    elif row < n :\n        spaces = \" \" * (2 * (n - 1))\n        each_row = spaces + \"*\"\n    else:\n        each_row = \"*\"\n    \n    print(each_row)",
      "language": "PYTHON",
      "default_code": true
    }
  ],
